SIMPLE: flown
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flown
<hw>Flown</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <def><pos>p. p.</pos> of <er>Fly</er>; --
often used with the auxiliary verb <xex>to be</xex>; <as>as, the birds
are <ex>flown</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flown</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Flown
<hw>Flown</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Flushed, inflated.</def>
<note>[Supposed by some to be a mistake for <xex>blown</xex> or
<xex>swoln</xex>.]</note> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then wander forth the sons⟦br⟧
Of Belial, <qex>flown</qex> with insolence and wine.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Floxed silk</ent>⟦br⟧
